      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces and add to a baking tray[s]</p><p>Drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>then<strong> </strong>add your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 30-35 min or until crisp and cooked through – these are your <strong>turmeric roast potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice half your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>remaining red onion</strong> as finely as you can</p><p>Dice your <strong>tomato[es]</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p><p>While the onion softens, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with your<strong> ground cumin</strong>,<strong> ground coriander</strong> and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> to the pan with your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> lamb mince</strong> and cook for a further 4-5 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Tip: Spoon off any excess fat that may come out of the meat</p><p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1832Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
